      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed on the pedicle screw–rod assembly. QoI (stiffness, yield force) changed by less than 1.3% between the medium and fine mesh. The medium mesh was selected for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Force and displacement residuals converge below 1e-4 for all load steps.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson iteration residuals monitored across all 40 load increments. Maximum residual was 3.2e-5, well below the 1e-4 threshold. No non-convergence events were recorded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup, boundary conditions, and load application by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "A second analyst independently reviewed all boundary condition definitions, contact pair assignments, and load application sequences. No discrepancies were identified relative to the analysis plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic material model with nonlinear geometry (large deformation) enabled; contact modeled as frictional (mu=0.2). Justified by prior literature and material coupon data.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V screw and UHMWPE block material properties assigned from published coupon data. Large-deformation formulation enabled to capture geometric nonlinearity at 40 mm displacement. Frictional contact coefficient validated against published screw–block interface studies."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometry dimensions, and boundary conditions traceable to certified measurement reports.",
      "rationale": "Screw geometry digitized from certified CMM reports (±5 µm tolerance). Material elastic modulus and yield strength from certified coupon test certificates. Block dimensions from ASTM F1717 standard. All inputs documented in the analysis plan with traceability references."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from production lots, tested across two independent laboratories.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from two production lots were tested: six at Lab 1 and five at Lab 2. Lot traceability and certificate of conformance records are on file. Sample size meets the minimum specified in the analysis plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinical loading scenarios including at least two load levels.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single static compression-bending load condition per ASTM F1717. Only one test condition was evaluated; dynamic and multi-axial conditions were not included. This factor is below the required level and is documented as a known gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters match test specimen measurements within measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Screw dimensions used in the FEA were taken from CMM measurements of the actual tested specimens. Block stiffness was matched to lot-specific durometer readings. Input equivalency confirmed for all primary QoI-driving parameters."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Percent difference <10% for all QoIs across both laboratories; E/uval <1.96.",
      "rationale": "All five validation comparisons (stiffness and yield force at Lab 1, stiffness and yield force at Lab 2, force at 40 mm at Lab 1) show percent differences between 3.9% and 7.5%, all within the 10% acceptance bound. E/uval metric was not formally computed due to absence of UQ on validation results, but nominal differences are well within bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly relevant to the clinical failure modes of interest.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement directly correspond to fatigue and fracture failure thresholds documented in the device risk analysis. All three QoIs are clinically and regulatorily relevant."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
